# Jyotish AI - Cursor Rules

## Project Context
This is a Vedic astrology SaaS platform that generates personalized birth chart analyses and forecasts using AI.

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 14 App Router
- TypeScript (strict mode)
- Supabase (auth + database)
- Stripe (payments)
- Anthropic Claude API
- Tailwind CSS + Shadcn/ui

## Code Style

### TypeScript
- Use strict TypeScript
- Avoid `any` types - use proper interfaces from `src/types/index.ts`
- Prefer type inference where obvious
- Use `unknown` for truly unknown types

### React/Next.js
- Use Server Components by default
- Mark Client Components with 'use client' only when needed (for interactivity, hooks, browser APIs)
- Use async/await for server components that fetch data
- Prefer Server Actions over API routes for mutations when possible

### Component Organization
- Place reusable UI in `components/ui/` (shadcn components)
- Domain-specific components in `components/[domain]/`
- Shared components in `components/shared/`

### API Routes
- Validate user auth in protected routes
- Use proper HTTP status codes
- Return consistent JSON structure: `{ success: boolean, data?: any, error?: string }`
- Handle errors gracefully with try-catch

### Supabase
- Use `createClient()` from `@/lib/supabase/server` in Server Components
- Use `createClient()` from `@/lib/supabase/client` in Client Components
- Always check auth state before database operations
- Leverage RLS policies for security

### AI Agents
- Each agent has a specific, focused responsibility
- Use clear, detailed prompts with context
- Handle rate limits and errors gracefully
- Log agent calls for debugging

### Styling
- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes
- Follow shadcn/ui design patterns
- Use Framer Motion for animations sparingly
- Ensure responsive design (mobile-first)

## Naming Conventions
- Files: camelCase for utilities, PascalCase for components
- Functions: camelCase, descriptive names
- Types/Interfaces: PascalCase
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE

## Security
- Never expose API keys in client code
- Use RLS policies in Supabase
- Validate all user input
- Sanitize data before AI prompts

## Performance
- Use Server Components to reduce client JS
- Implement loading states for async operations
- Optimize images with Next.js Image component
- Lazy load heavy components

## Vedic Astrology Terminology
- Use traditional Sanskrit terms where appropriate
- Provide context/tooltips for non-expert users
- Follow authentic Vedic astrology principles
- Cite classical texts when relevant
